  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Head of Membership",
  "description": "<h3>Who We Are</h3><p>The Nanson is a private members’ club in Singapore, blending social, work, and cultural experiences. Through curated events, conversations, and collaborations, we create moments that stimulate both intellect and the senses.</p><h3>The Role</h3><p>The Head of Membership leads the club’s membership strategy, growth, and engagement. This role oversees acquisition, retention, partnerships, reciprocal clubs, and curated member experiences, while leading the Membership & Engagement team to deliver an exceptional, values-aligned member journey.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p>Membership Strategy & Growth</p><ul><li><p>Drive membership acquisition, onboarding, retention, and engagement</p></li><li><p>Own membership P&L, KPIs, reporting, and performance insights</p></li><li><p>Analyse trends to inform strategic decisions</p></li></ul><p>Partnerships, Perks & Reciprocal Clubs</p><ul><li><p>Build strategic partnerships and co-branded activations</p></li><li><p>Oversee member perks and reciprocal club relationships globally</p></li><li><p>Evaluate partnerships to ensure value, alignment, and impact</p></li></ul><p>Community & Engagement</p><ul><li><p>Cultivate a vibrant, inclusive member community</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong on-floor presence and member relationships</p></li><li><p>Identify and nurture member ambassadors</p></li></ul><p>Co-Working Management</p><ul><li><p>Oversee co-working performance, revenue, and engagement</p></li><li><p>Drive tenant community-building and reporting</p></li></ul><p>Systems & Processes</p><ul><li><p>Oversee CRM, reporting accuracy, and membership operations</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with Marketing on member communications</p></li><li><p>Continuously improve membership systems and workflows</p></li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li><p>Min 5 years of experience in either business development/ growth/ sales in an hospitality environment (ie. hotels, MICE, private members club, etc)</p></li><li><p>Proven success in driving revenue</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication, interpersonal, and negotiation skills.</p></li><li><p>A deep understanding of luxury service standards and high-net-worth clientele.</p></li><li><p>Passion for community building, culture, and experiences that connect people meaningfully.</p></li></ul><p>Your Perks</p><ul><li><p>5-day work week with diverse and energetic colleagues who work hard and play hard</p></li><li><p>Employee discount on F&B at the club</p></li><li><p>Daily staff meals (Breakfast to Dinner)</p></li><li><p>Group Insurance ( GP- unlimited free consultation & medicine, TCM, Hospitalisation)</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
